title: The Coldest Regulatory Climate on Earth
text:
Royal Dutch Shell announced on Monday that it will stop exploring for oil and gas off Alaska’s Arctic coast. Environmental groups are cheering, but Shell’s retreat is a loss for the Alaskan economy and U.S. energy production.
The company reports that a recent exploratory well yielded “indications of oil and gas” that were “not sufficient to warrant further exploration.” At least not when such projects have to carry the burden of...
